'''Crew''' play an important role in [[Star Trek Timelines]]. Crew can be placed in battle stations on [[Ships]]. Each [[Missions|Mission]] begins with players select crew for an away team, with different crew being better suited for different situations. Each character is proficient in at least one [[skill]]: [[Diplomacy]], [[Science]], [[Security]], [[Command]], [[Engineering]] and [[Medicine]]. To complete a mission, characters will need to meet certain skill requirements, for example 22 Security. Skills can be improved by adding equipment, and fusing characters with extra copies of themselves. Crew also have inherent abilities called [[traits]]. For example, [[Defiant Commander Worf]] has the ''[[Tactician]]'' trait. Traits provide a bonus when playing missions. Traits can also unlock options during Conflict Missions, for example being human may help crew relate to human enemies and allies. By completing conflicts, players can gain crew experience, credits, equipment, and many other items. Completing conflicts is a key way to improve crew in Star Trek Timelines. Due to the timeline anomaly, central to the story of Star Trek Timelines, there are multiple versions of some characters. For example, there are currently five versions of Kathryn Janeway: [[Captain Janeway]], [[Rifle Janeway]], [[Admiral Janeway]], [[Warship Janeway]], and [[Arachnia Janeway|Queen Arachnia]]. It is hoped that further characters will be added to Star Trek Timelines after the game's release http://pocketnow.com/2015/03/07/star-trek-timelines-pax-east-2015. Some characters might be added during global events or special occasions https://www.disruptorbeam.com/blog/entry/live-friday-the-disruptor-stream-featuring-star-trek-timelines __TOC__ == Crew advancement == ==== Power & levels ==== The skill potential of crew characters depends on levels (1 to 100), rarity (common to legendary, representing the maximum number of stars available to the crew) and star rating (how many stars are actually filled). It is also increased by equipping items. Leveling is achieved when a character gains Experience, either by participating in missions or using the "Train" button in the "Manage Crew" screen. Every ten levels the crew needs to equip all his four items and ''Advance'' before they can gain more experience. Characters of greater than Uncommon rarity (2+ stars, green border) require duplicate (identical) crew characters to be [[fused]] (to join together) to increase their star power. For more info, please refer to the [[Crew Progression]] page. ==== Equipment ==== There are a variety of ways crew can become be improved. One of the best ways is to equip them with items. Each item can be either found (in a specific mission) or built (from parts). Tap on each of the 4 item slots to see where each item can be found or how it can be built (see next section). Once all four items are equipped, the character can be Advanced which increases the level cap by 10 and resets the equipment slots. There is a bug that makes it so that you can see an item in your [[inventory]], but in the crew management screen it says you still need to get it."Not able to equip/build an item you believe you have? Workaround here (Sticky please)" https://www.disruptorbeam.com/forums/stt/viewthread/47737/ ==== Building items ==== Some items that a crew character needs to equip must be built. Tapping on the "Build" button shows the required components in order to build the item. Tapping on each component will show the mission(s) needed to get each component. == Crew Capacity == There is a limit to the number of crew members players may have at a time, this starts at 25. Note that it may not be necessary to dismiss crew you'd like to keep. The [[Cryostasis Vault]] can be used to "store" fully levelled, fully fused crew members, so they no longer block crew slots. === Effects === If you are one below capacity and you attempt to claim crew via [[Daily Rewards]] on your [[VIP]] double reward day, you will only get one copy of that crewman. It is unknown if you can claim crew while being at or above capacity or whether you forfeit the prize entirely. You may still be able to get crew from the [[Time Portal]] above your capacity, however you will not be able to use, train, or equip items to crew obtained after you reached capacity. Such crew will also be automatically dismissed if you are not at or below capacity within 7 days. Note that locked crew may still be fused as long as one copy of the crewman is unlocked. === Unlocking slots === A person can unlock more crew slots from: * Purchasing crew slots directly for {{Currency|crd}}https://www.disruptorbeam.com/forums/stt/viewthread/50182/ then {{Currency|dil}}https://startrektimelines.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/217798798-How-can-I-purchase-more-crew-slots- (once your Available Crew has gone over its limitnot before hand), * Or indirectly by accumulating [[VIP|VIP Levels]]https://startrektimelines.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/216254948-VIP-Bonus-crew-slots-explained from the purchase of {{Currency|dil}} As of June 16, 2016, there are a max of 180 crew slots.
